msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1607 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2713
msgid "C<hvvalue> can be NULL."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1609
msgid "copy-attributes"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1611
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" copy-attributes src dest [all:true|false] [mode:true|false] [xattributes:true|false] [ownership:true|false]\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1613 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2737
msgid ""
"Copy the attributes of a path (which can be a file or a directory)  to "
"another path."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1616 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2740
msgid ""
"By default C<no> attribute is copied, so make sure to specify any (or C<all> "
"to copy everything)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1619 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2743
msgid "The optional arguments specify which attributes can be copied:"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1623 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2747
msgid "C<mode>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1625 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2749
msgid ""
"Copy part of the file mode from C<source> to C<destination>. Only the UNIX "
"permissions and the sticky/setuid/setgid bits can be copied."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1628 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2752
msgid "C<xattributes>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1630
msgid ""
"Copy the Linux extended attributes (xattrs) from C<source> to "
"C<destination>.  This flag does nothing if the I<linuxxattrs> feature is not "
"available (see L</feature-available>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1634 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2758
msgid "C<ownership>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1636 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2760
msgid "Copy the owner uid and the group gid of C<source> to C<destination>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1638 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2762
msgid "C<all>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1640 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2764
msgid ""
"Copy B<all> the attributes from C<source> to C<destination>. Enabling it "
"enables all the other flags, if they are not specified already."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1647
msgid "copy-device-to-device"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1649
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" copy-device-to-device src dest [srcoffset:N] [destoffset:N] [size:N] [sparse:true|false] [append:true|false]\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1651
msgid ""
"The four calls L</copy-device-to-device>, L</copy-device-to-file>, L</copy-"
"file-to-device>, and L</copy-file-to-file> let you copy from a source "
"(device|file) to a destination (device|file)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1658 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2823
msgid ""
"Partial copies can be made since you can specify optionally the source "
"offset, destination offset and size to copy.  These values are all specified "
"in bytes.  If not given, the offsets both default to zero, and the size "
"defaults to copying as much as possible until we hit the end of the source."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1664 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2829
msgid ""
"The source and destination may be the same object.  However overlapping "
"regions may not be copied correctly."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1667 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2832
msgid ""
"If the destination is a file, it is created if required.  If the destination "
"file is not large enough, it is extended."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1670 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2835
msgid ""
"If the destination is a file and the C<append> flag is not set, then the "
"destination file is truncated.  If the C<append> flag is set, then the copy "
"appends to the destination file.  The C<append> flag currently cannot be set "
"for devices."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1675 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:2840
msgid ""
"If the C<sparse> flag is true then the call avoids writing blocks that "
"contain only zeroes, which can help in some situations where the backing "
"disk is thin-provisioned.  Note that unless the target is already zeroed, "
"using this option will result in incorrect copying."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1683
msgid "copy-device-to-file"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1685
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" copy-device-to-file src dest [srcoffset:N] [destoffset:N] [size:N] [sparse:true|false] [append:true|false]\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1687 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1696
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1705
msgid "See L</copy-device-to-device> for a general overview of this call."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1692
msgid "copy-file-to-device"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1694
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" copy-file-to-device src dest [srcoffset:N] [destoffset:N] [size:N] [sparse:true|false] [append:true|false]\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1701
msgid "copy-file-to-file"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1703
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" copy-file-to-file src dest [srcoffset:N] [destoffset:N] [size:N] [sparse:true|false] [append:true|false]\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1708
msgid ""
"This is B<not> the function you want for copying files.  This is for copying "
"blocks within existing files.  See L</cp>, L</cp-a> and L</mv> for general "
"file copying and moving functions."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1715
msgid "copy-size"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1717
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" copy-size src dest size\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" copy-size src dest size\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1719 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3102
msgid ""
"This command copies exactly C<size> bytes from one source device or file "
"C<src> to another destination device or file C<dest>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1722 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3105
msgid ""
"Note this will fail if the source is too short or if the destination is not "
"large enough."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1725 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1801
msgid ""
"I<This function is deprecated.> In new code, use the L</copy-device-to-"
"device> call instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1732
msgid "cp"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1734
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" cp src dest\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" cp src dest\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1736 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3124
msgid ""
"This copies a file from C<src> to C<dest> where C<dest> is either a "
"destination filename or destination directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1739
msgid "cp-a"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1741
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" cp-a src dest\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" cp-a src dest\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1743 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3138
msgid ""
"This copies a file or directory from C<src> to C<dest> recursively using the "
"C<cp -a> command."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1746
msgid "cp-r"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1748
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" cp-r src dest\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" cp-r src dest\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1750 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3152
msgid ""
"This copies a file or directory from C<src> to C<dest> recursively using the "
"C<cp -rP> command."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1753
msgid ""
"Most users should use L</cp-a> instead.  This command is useful when you "
"don't want to preserve permissions, because the target filesystem does not "
"support it (primarily when writing to DOS FAT filesystems)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1758
msgid "cpio-out"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1760
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" cpio-out directory (cpiofile|-) [format:..]\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1762 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3179
msgid ""
"This command packs the contents of F<directory> and downloads it to local "
"file C<cpiofile>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1765 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3182
msgid ""
"The optional C<format> parameter can be used to select the format.  Only the "
"following formats are currently permitted:"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1770 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3187
msgid "C<newc>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1772 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3189
msgid ""
"New (SVR4) portable format.  This format happens to be compatible with the "
"cpio-like format used by the Linux kernel for initramfs."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1775 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3192
msgid "This is the default format."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1779 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3196
msgid "New (SVR4) portable format with a checksum."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1787
msgid "dd"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1789
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" dd src dest\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" dd src dest\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1791 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3242
msgid ""
"This command copies from one source device or file C<src> to another "
"destination device or file C<dest>.  Normally you would use this to copy to "
"or from a device or partition, for example to duplicate a filesystem."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1796
msgid ""
"If the destination is a device, it must be as large or larger than the "
"source file or device, otherwise the copy will fail.  This command cannot do "
"partial copies (see L</copy-device-to-device>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1808
msgid "device-index"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1810
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" device-index device\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" device-index device\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1812 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3262
msgid ""
"This function takes a device name (eg. \"/dev/sdb\") and returns the index "
"of the device in the list of devices."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1815
msgid ""
"Index numbers start from 0.  The named device must exist, for example as a "
"string returned from L</list-devices>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1818
msgid "See also L</list-devices>, L</part-to-dev>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1820
msgid "df"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1822
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" df\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" df\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1824 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3279
msgid "This command runs the C<df> command to report disk space used."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1826 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1837
msgid ""
"This command is mostly useful for interactive sessions.  It is I<not> "
"intended that you try to parse the output string.  Use L</statvfs> from "
"programs."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1830
msgid "df-h"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1832
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" df-h\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" df-h\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1834 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3295
msgid ""
"This command runs the C<df -h> command to report disk space used in human-"
"readable format."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1841
msgid "disk-create"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1843
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" disk-create filename format size [backingfile:..] [backingformat:..] [preallocation:..] [compat:..] [clustersize:N]\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1845 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3327
msgid ""
"Create a blank disk image called F<filename> (a host file)  with format "
"C<format> (usually C<raw> or C<qcow2>).  The size is C<size> bytes."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1849 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3331
msgid ""
"If used with the optional C<backingfile> parameter, then a snapshot is "
"created on top of the backing file.  In this case, C<size> must be passed as "
"C<-1>.  The size of the snapshot is the same as the size of the backing "
"file, which is discovered automatically.  You are encouraged to also pass "
"C<backingformat> to describe the format of C<backingfile>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1856 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3338
msgid ""
"If F<filename> refers to a block device, then the device is formatted.  The "
"C<size> is ignored since block devices have an intrinsic size."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1860 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3342
msgid "The other optional parameters are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1864 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3346
msgid "C<preallocation>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1866 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3348
msgid ""
"If format is C<raw>, then this can be either C<off> (or C<sparse>)  or "
"C<full> to create a sparse or fully allocated file respectively.  The "
"default is C<off>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1870 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3352
msgid ""
"If format is C<qcow2>, then this can be C<off> (or C<sparse>), C<metadata> "
"or C<full>.  Preallocating metadata can be faster when doing lots of writes, "
"but uses more space.  The default is C<off>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1875 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3357
msgid "C<compat>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1877 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3359
msgid ""
"C<qcow2> only: Pass the string C<1.1> to use the advanced qcow2 format "
"supported by qemu E<ge> 1.1."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1881 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3363
msgid "C<clustersize>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1883 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3365
msgid ""
"C<qcow2> only: Change the qcow2 cluster size.  The default is 65536 (bytes) "
"and this setting may be any power of two between 512 and 2097152."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1889
msgid ""
"Note that this call does not add the new disk to the handle.  You may need "
"to call L</add-drive-opts> separately."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1894
msgid "disk-format"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1896
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" disk-format filename\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" disk-format filename\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1898 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3410
msgid ""
"Detect and return the format of the disk image called F<filename>.  "
"F<filename> can also be a host device, etc.  If the format of the image "
"could not be detected, then C<\"unknown\"> is returned."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1902 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3414
msgid ""
"Note that detecting the disk format can be insecure under some "
"circumstances.  See L<guestfs(3)/CVE-2010-3851>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1905 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3417
msgid "See also: L<guestfs(3)/DISK IMAGE FORMATS>"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1907
msgid "disk-has-backing-file"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1909
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" disk-has-backing-file filename\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" disk-has-backing-file filename\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1911 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3430
msgid ""
"Detect and return whether the disk image F<filename> has a backing file."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1914 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1924
#: ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3433 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3449
msgid ""
"Note that detecting disk features can be insecure under some circumstances.  "
"See L<guestfs(3)/CVE-2010-3851>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1917
msgid "disk-virtual-size"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1919
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" disk-virtual-size filename\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" disk-virtual-size filename\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1921 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3446
msgid ""
"Detect and return the virtual size in bytes of the disk image called "
"F<filename>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1927
msgid "dmesg"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1929
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" dmesg\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" dmesg\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1931 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3461
msgid ""
"This returns the kernel messages (C<dmesg> output) from the guest kernel.  "
"This is sometimes useful for extended debugging of problems."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1935
msgid ""
"Another way to get the same information is to enable verbose messages with "
"L</set-verbose> or by setting the environment variable C<LIBGUESTFS_DEBUG=1> "
"before running the program."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1940
msgid "download"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1942
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" download remotefilename (filename|-)\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" download remotefilename (filename|-)\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1944 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1957
#: ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3482 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3507
msgid ""
"Download file F<remotefilename> and save it as F<filename> on the local "
"machine."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1947 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:8219
#: ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3485 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:13627
msgid "F<filename> can also be a named pipe."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1949
msgid "See also L</upload>, L</cat>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1953
msgid "download-offset"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1955
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" download-offset remotefilename (filename|-) offset size\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" download-offset remotefilename (filename|-) offset size\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1960 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3510
msgid ""
"F<remotefilename> is read for C<size> bytes starting at C<offset> (this "
"region must be within the file or device)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1963
msgid ""
"Note that there is no limit on the amount of data that can be downloaded "
"with this call, unlike with L</pread>, and this call always reads the full "
"amount unless an error occurs."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1968
msgid "See also L</download>, L</pread>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1972
msgid "drop-caches"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1974
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" drop-caches whattodrop\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" drop-caches whattodrop\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1976 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3535
msgid ""
"This instructs the guest kernel to drop its page cache, and/or dentries and "
"inode caches.  The parameter C<whattodrop> tells the kernel what precisely "
"to drop, see L<http://linux-mm.org/Drop_Caches>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1981 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3540
msgid "Setting C<whattodrop> to 3 should drop everything."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1983 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3542
msgid ""
"This automatically calls L<sync(2)> before the operation, so that the "
"maximum guest memory is freed."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1986
msgid "du"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1988
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" du path\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" du path\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1990 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3555
msgid ""
"This command runs the C<du -s> command to estimate file space usage for "
"C<path>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1993 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3558
msgid ""
"C<path> can be a file or a directory.  If C<path> is a directory then the "
"estimate includes the contents of the directory and all subdirectories "
"(recursively)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:1997 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3562
msgid ""
"The result is the estimated size in I<kilobytes> (ie. units of 1024 bytes)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2000
msgid "e2fsck"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2002
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" e2fsck device [correct:true|false] [forceall:true|false]\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" e2fsck device [correct:true|false] [forceall:true|false]\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2004 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3589
msgid ""
"This runs the ext2/ext3 filesystem checker on C<device>.  It can take the "
"following optional arguments:"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2009 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3594
msgid "C<correct>"
msgstr "C<correct>"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2011 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3596
msgid ""
"Automatically repair the file system. This option will cause e2fsck to "
"automatically fix any filesystem problems that can be safely fixed without "
"human intervention."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2015 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3600
msgid ""
"This option may not be specified at the same time as the C<forceall> option."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2017 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3602
msgid "C<forceall>"
msgstr "C<forceall>"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2019 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3604
msgid ""
"Assume an answer of 'yes' to all questions; allows e2fsck to be used non-"
"interactively."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2022 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3607
msgid ""
"This option may not be specified at the same time as the C<correct> option."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2028
msgid "e2fsck-f"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2030
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" e2fsck-f device\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" e2fsck-f device\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2032 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3650
msgid ""
"This runs C<e2fsck -p -f device>, ie. runs the ext2/ext3 filesystem checker "
"on C<device>, noninteractively (I<-p>), even if the filesystem appears to be "
"clean (I<-f>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2036
msgid ""
"I<This function is deprecated.> In new code, use the L</e2fsck> call instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2043
msgid "echo-daemon"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2045
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" echo-daemon 'words ...'\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" echo-daemon 'words ...'\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2047 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3664
msgid ""
"This command concatenates the list of C<words> passed with single spaces "
"between them and returns the resulting string."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2050 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3667
msgid "You can use this command to test the connection through to the daemon."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2052
msgid "See also L</ping-daemon>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2054
msgid "egrep"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2056
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" egrep regex path\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" egrep regex path\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2058 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3690
msgid ""
"This calls the external C<egrep> program and returns the matching lines."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2064 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2081
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2189 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2206
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:3057 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:8656
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:8673 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:8748
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:8765 ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:8801
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:8818
msgid ""
"I<This function is deprecated.> In new code, use the L</grep> call instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2071
msgid "egrepi"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2073
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" egrepi regex path\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" egrepi regex path\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2075 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3716
msgid ""
"This calls the external C<egrep -i> program and returns the matching lines."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2088
msgid "equal"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2090
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" equal file1 file2\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" equal file1 file2\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2092 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3735
msgid ""
"This compares the two files F<file1> and F<file2> and returns true if their "
"content is exactly equal, or false otherwise."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2095 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3738
msgid "The external L<cmp(1)> program is used for the comparison."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2097
msgid "exists"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2099
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" exists path\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" exists path\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2101 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3750
msgid ""
"This returns C<true> if and only if there is a file, directory (or anything) "
"with the given C<path> name."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2104
msgid "See also L</is-file>, L</is-dir>, L</stat>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2106
msgid "extlinux"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2108
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" extlinux directory\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
" extlinux directory\n"
"\n"

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2110
msgid ""
"Install the SYSLINUX bootloader on the device mounted at F<directory>.  "
"Unlike L</syslinux> which requires a FAT filesystem, this can be used on an "
"ext2/3/4 or btrfs filesystem."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2114 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3769
msgid ""
"The F<directory> parameter can be either a mountpoint, or a directory within "
"the mountpoint."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2117
msgid ""
"You also have to mark the partition as \"active\" (L</part-set-bootable>) "
"and a Master Boot Record must be installed (eg. using L</pwrite-device>) on "
"the first sector of the whole disk.  The SYSLINUX package comes with some "
"suitable Master Boot Records.  See the L<extlinux(1)> man page for further "
"information."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../fish/guestfish-actions.pod:2124 ../src/guestfs-actions.pod:3779
msgid ""
"Additional configuration can be supplied to SYSLINUX by placing a file "
"called F<extlinux.conf> on the filesystem under F<directory>.  For further "
"information about the contents of this file, see L<extlinux(1)>."
