#. type: =head1
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:279
msgid "KERNEL COMMAND LINE CONFIGURATION"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:281
msgid ""
"If you don't want to configure things using the graphical UI, an alternative "
"is to configure through the kernel command line.  This is especially "
"convenient if you are converting a lot of physical machines which are booted "
"using PXE."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:286
msgid ""
"Where exactly you set command line arguments depends on your PXE "
"implementation, but for pxelinux you put them in the C<APPEND> field in the "
"F<pxelinux.cfg> file.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:290
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" DEFAULT p2v\n"
" TIMEOUT 20\n"
" PROMPT 0\n"
" LABEL p2v\n"
"   KERNEL vmlinuz0\n"
"   APPEND initrd=initrd0.img [....] p2v.server=conv.example.com p2v.password=secret p2v.o=libvirt\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:297
msgid "You have to set some or all of the following command line arguments:"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:301
msgid "B<p2v.server=SERVER>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:303
msgid "The name or IP address of the conversion server."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:305
msgid ""
"This is always required if you are using the kernel configuration method.  "
"If virt-p2v does not find this on the kernel command line then it switches "
"to the GUI (interactive) configuration method."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:309
msgid "B<p2v.port=NN>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:311
msgid "The SSH port number on the conversion server (default: C<22>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:313
msgid "B<p2v.username=USERNAME>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:315
msgid ""
"The SSH username that we log in as on the conversion server (default: "
"C<root>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:318
msgid "B<p2v.password=PASSWORD>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:320
msgid "The SSH password that we use to log in to the conversion server."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:322
msgid ""
"The default is to try with no password.  If this fails then virt-p2v will "
"ask the user to type the password (probably several times during conversion)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:326
msgid "This setting is ignored if C<p2v.identity> is present."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:328
msgid "B<p2v.identity=URL>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:330
msgid ""
"Provide a URL pointing to an SSH identity (private key) file.  The URL is "
"interpreted by L<curl(1)> so any URL that curl supports can be used here, "
"including C<https://> and C<file://>.  For more information on using SSH "
"identities, see L</SSH IDENTITIES> below."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:335
msgid ""
"If C<p2v.identity> is present, it overrides C<p2v.password>.  There is no "
"fallback."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:338
msgid "B<p2v.sudo>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:340
msgid ""
"Use C<p2v.sudo> to tell virt-p2v to use L<sudo(8)> to gain root privileges "
"on the conversion server after logging in as a non-root user (default: do "
"not use sudo)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:344
msgid "B<p2v.name=GUESTNAME>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:346
msgid ""
"The name of the guest that is created.  The default is to try to derive a "
"name from the physical machine's hostname (if possible) else use a randomly "
"generated name."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:350
msgid "B<p2v.vcpus=NN>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:352
msgid ""
"The number of virtual CPUs to give to the guest.  The default is to use the "
"same as the number of physical CPUs."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:355
msgid "B<p2v.memory=NN(M|G)>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:357
msgid ""
"The size of the guest memory.  You must specify the unit as either megabytes "
"or gigabytes by using (eg) C<p2v.memory=1024M> or C<p2v.memory=1G>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:361
msgid ""
"The default is to use the same amount of RAM as on the physical machine."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:364
msgid "B<p2v.debug>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:366
msgid "Use this to enable full debugging of virt-v2v."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:368
msgid ""
"If asked to diagnose a problem with virt-p2v, you should add C<p2v.debug> to "
"the kernel command line, and examine the log file which is left in F</tmp> "
"on the conversion server."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:372
msgid "B<p2v.disks=sdX,sdY,..>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:374
msgid "A list of physical hard disks to convert, for example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:376
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" p2v.disks=sda,sdc\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:378
msgid "The default is to convert all local hard disks that are found."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:380
msgid "B<p2v.removable=srX,srY,..>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:382
msgid ""
"A list of removable media to convert.  The default is to create virtual "
"removable devices for every physical removable device found.  Note that the "
"content of removable media is never copied over."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:386
msgid "B<p2v.interfaces=em1,..>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:388
msgid ""
"A list of network interfaces to convert.  The default is to create virtual "
"network interfaces for every physical network interface found."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:391
msgid "B<p2v.network=interface:target,...>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:393
msgid ""
"Controls how network interfaces are connected to virtual networks on the "
"target hypervisor.  The default is to connect all network interfaces to the "
"target C<default> network."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:397
msgid ""
"You give a comma-separated list of C<interface:target> pairs, plus "
"optionally a default target.  For example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:400
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" p2v.network=em1:rhevm\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:402
msgid "maps interface C<em1> to target network C<rhevm>."
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:404
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" p2v.network=em1:rhevm,em2:management,other\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:406
msgid ""
"maps interface C<em1> to C<rhevm>, and C<em2> to C<management>, and any "
"other interface that is found to C<other>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:409
msgid "B<p2v.o=[libvirt|local|...]>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:411
msgid ""
"Set the output mode.  This is the same as the virt-v2v I<-o> option.  See "
"L<virt-v2v(1)/OPTIONS>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:414
msgid ""
"If not specified, the default is C<local>, and the converted guest is "
"written to F</var/tmp>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:417
msgid "B<p2v.oa=sparse|preallocated>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:419
msgid ""
"Set the output allocation mode.  This is the same as the virt-v2v I<-oa> "
"option.  See L<virt-v2v(1)/OPTIONS>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:422
msgid "B<p2v.oc=...>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:424
msgid ""
"Set the output connection libvirt URI.  This is the same as the virt-v2v I<-"
"oc> option.  See L<virt-v2v(1)/OPTIONS> and L<http://libvirt.org/uri.html>"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:428
msgid "B<p2v.of=raw|qcow2|...>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:430
msgid ""
"Set the output format.  This is the same as the virt-v2v I<-of> option.  See "
"L<virt-v2v(1)/OPTIONS>."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:433
msgid "B<p2v.os=...>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:435
msgid ""
"Set the output storage.  This is the same as the virt-v2v I<-os> option.  "
"See L<virt-v2v(1)/OPTIONS>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:438
msgid ""
"If not specified, the default is F</var/tmp> (on the conversion server)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:440
msgid "B<p2v.pre=COMMAND>"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:442
msgid "B<p2v.pre=\"COMMAND ARG ...\">"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:444
msgid ""
"Select a pre-conversion command to run.  Any command or script can be "
"specified here.  If the command contains spaces, you must quote the whole "
"command with double quotes.  The default is not to run any command."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:449
msgid "B<p2v.post=poweroff>"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:451
msgid "B<p2v.post=reboot>"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:453
msgid "B<p2v.post=COMMAND>"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:455
msgid "B<p2v.post=\"COMMAND ARG ...\">"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:457
msgid ""
"Select a post-conversion command to run if conversion is successful.  This "
"can be any command or script.  If the command contains spaces, you must "
"quote the whole command with double quotes."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:461
msgid ""
"I<If> virt-p2v is running as root, I<and> the command line was set from F</"
"proc/cmdline> (not I<--cmdline>), then the default is to run the "
"L<poweroff(8)> command.  Otherwise the default is not to run any command."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:466
msgid "B<p2v.fail=COMMAND>"
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:468
msgid "B<p2v.fail=\"COMMAND ARG ...\">"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:470
msgid ""
"Select a post-conversion command to run if conversion fails.  Any command or "
"script can be specified here.  If the command contains spaces, you must "
"quote the whole command with double quotes.  The default is not to run any "
"command."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:475
msgid "B<ip=dhcp>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:477
msgid "Use DHCP for configuring the network interface (this is the default)."
msgstr ""

#. type: =item
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:481
msgid "B<ip=ADDR:GATEWAY:NETMASK>"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:483
msgid "Set up a static IPv4 network configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head1
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:489
msgid "SSH IDENTITIES"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:491
msgid ""
"As a somewhat more secure alternative to password authentication, you can "
"use an SSH identity (private key) for authentication."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:498
msgid ""
"This creates a private key (C<id_rsa>) and a public key (C<id_rsa.pub>) pair."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:501
msgid ""
"The public key should be appended to the C<authorized_keys> file on the virt-"
"v2v conversion server (usually to C</root/.ssh/authorized_keys>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:505
msgid ""
"For distributing the private key, there are four scenarios from least secure "
"to most secure:"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:512
msgid "Not using SSH identities at all, ie. password authentication."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:514
msgid ""
"Anyone who can sniff the PXE boot parameters from the network or observe the "
"password some other way can log in to the virt-v2v conversion server."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:520
msgid ""
"SSH identity embedded in the virt-p2v ISO or disk image.  In the GUI, use:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../p2v/virt-p2v.pod:522
