#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:3
msgid "virt-v2v-copy-to-local - Copy a remote guest to the local machine"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:7
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" virt-v2v-copy-to-local -ic LIBVIRT_URI GUEST\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:9
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" virt-v2v-copy-to-local -ic xen+ssh://root@xen.example.com xen_guest\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" virt-v2v-copy-to-local -ic esx://root@esxi.example.com vmware_guest\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:15
msgid ""
"C<virt-v2v-copy-to-local> copies a guest from a remote hypervisor to the "
"local machine, in preparation for conversion by L<virt-v2v(1)>.  Note this "
"tool alone B<does not> do the virt-v2v conversion."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:19
msgid "When to use this tool"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:21
msgid ""
"This tool is not usually necessary, but there are a few special cases (see "
"list below) where you might need it."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:24
msgid ""
"If your case does not fit one of these special cases, then ignore this tool "
"and read L<virt-v2v(1)> instead.  The virt-v2v-copy-to-local process is "
"slower than using virt-v2v directly, because it has to copy unused parts of "
"the guest disk."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:33
msgid ""
"You have a Xen guest using host block devices.  Virt-v2v cannot convert such "
"guests directly."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:36
msgid "See L<virt-v2v(1)/XEN OR SSH CONVERSIONS FROM BLOCK DEVICES>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:40
msgid ""
"You have VMware ESXi hypervisors, and are not using VMware vCenter to manage "
"them.  Virt-v2v cannot directly access ESXi hypervisor, so you either have "
"to export the guest as an OVA (eg. using VMware's C<ovftool>); or you can "
"use this tool to copy the guest to a local file on the conversion server, "
"from where virt-v2v will be able to access it."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:49
msgid "How this tool works"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:51
msgid ""
"This tool uses libvirt to get the libvirt XML (metadata) of the remote "
"guest, essentially equivalent to running C<virsh dumpxml guest>."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:54
msgid ""
"It then uses the XML to locate the remote guest disks, which are copied over "
"using a hypervisor-specific method.  It uses ssh for remote Xen hypervisors, "
"and HTTPS (curl) for remote ESXi hypervisors."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:58
msgid ""
"It then modifies the libvirt XML so that it points at the local copies of "
"the guest disks."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:61
msgid ""
"The libvirt XML is output to a file called F<guest.xml> (where I<guest> is "
"the name of the guest).  The disk(s) are output to file(s)  called F<guest-"
"disk1>, F<guest-disk2> and so on."
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:65
msgid "After copying the guest locally, you can convert it using:"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:67
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" virt-v2v -i libvirtxml guest.xml [-o options ...]\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:69
msgid "Virt-v2v finds the local copies of the disks by looking in the XML."
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:73
msgid "Copy and convert from Xen hypervisor that uses host block devices"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:75
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" virt-v2v-copy-to-local -ic xen+ssh://root@xen.example.com xen_guest\n"
" virt-v2v -i libvirtxml xen_guest.xml -o local -os /var/tmp\n"
" rm xen_guest.xml xen_guest-disk*\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:79
msgid "Copy and convert from ESXi hypervisor"
msgstr ""

#. type: verbatim
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:81
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
" virt-v2v-copy-to-local -ic esx://root@esxi.example.com?no_verify=1 vmware_guest\n"
" virt-v2v -i libvirtxml vmware_guest.xml -o local -os /var/tmp\n"
" rm vmware_guest.xml vmware_guest-disk*\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head1
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:85
msgid "COPYING FROM XEN HYPERVISOR"
msgstr ""

#. type: =head2
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:87
msgid "XEN: LIBVIRT URI"
msgstr ""

#. type: textblock
#: ../v2v/virt-v2v-copy-to-local.pod:89
msgid "The libvirt URI for remote Xen hosts will look something like this:"
msgstr ""

